Sentencas: La(Sr)Ga(Fe,Mg)O-3 exhibited the high oxide ion conductivity and the electrical power generating property of SOFC single cell using La0.7Sr0.3Ga0.7Fe0.2Mg0.1O3-delta (LSGFM) electrolyte was investigated in this study.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The transport number of oxide ion is almost 0.8 in LSGFM and so open circuit potential (OCV) is as low as 0.8 V OCV was strongly affected by anode materials and the highest OCV was achieved on Ni-Fe bimetallic anode.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The extremely high power density was achieved by using LSGFM for electrolyte of SOFC.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power densities of the cells can be elevated by coating with oxide ion conductor film at anode side.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density increased in the following order for coating film: LSGM > SDC > YSZ.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum power density of 197 and 100 mW/cm(2) can be achieved at 873 and 773 K, respectively, when LSGM film deposited on the anode side of LSGFM.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Therefore, LSGFM can be used as electrolyte of SOFC operating at intermediate temperature.
Titulo: High oxide ion conductivity in Fe and Mg doped LaGaO3 as the electrolyte of solid oxide fuel cells
